---

<section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
        <h1>Welcome to Kumar's Personal Website</h1>
        <p class="hero-text">Hi, I'm Kumar.A. I'm a passionate learner who loves to explore and create innovative solutions in the world of technology. All these advances in Generative AI is really exciting. Can I learn to use this effectively? Shall keep you posted. Cheers & Stay blessed</p>
        <div class="hero-buttons">
            <a href="/about" class="button primary">Learn More</a>
            <a href="/contact" class="button secondary">Get in Touch</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="featured-projects">
    <h2>Featured Projects</h2>
    <div class="project-grid">
        <div class="project-card">
            <h3>Project 1</h3>
            <p>learning to use AI code editor with proper prompting and commit to github repo and auto deploy to web server my Personal Website</p>
            <a href="/projects/project-1" class="read-more">Read More →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="project-card">
            <h3>Project 2</h3>
            <p>Building a modern blog with Eleventy and AI integration, featuring bilingual content and automated deployments.</p>
            <a href="/projects/project-2" class="read-more">Read More →</a>
        </div>
        <div class="project-card">
            <h3>Project 3</h3>
            <p>Your third project showcase. What makes this one special?</p>
            <a href="/projects/project-3" class="read-more">Read More →</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="latest-posts">
    <h2>Latest Blog Posts</h2>
    <div class="post-grid">
        {%- for post in collections.post -%}
        {% if loop.index0 < 3 %}
        <article class="post-card">
            <h3><a href="{{ post.url }}">{{ post.data.title }}</a></h3>
            <div class="post-meta">
            <time datetime="{{ post.date | dateIso }}">{{ post.date | dateReadable }}</time>
                {% if post.data.tags %}
                <div class="tags">
                    {% for tag in post.data.tags %}
                        {% if tag != "post" %}
                        <span class="tag">{{ tag }}</span>
                        {% endif %}
                    {% endfor %}
                </div>
                {% endif %}
            </div>
            {% if post.data.description %}
            <p>{{ post.data.description }}</p>
            {% endif %}
            <a href="{{ post.url }}" class="read-more">Read More →</a>
        </article>
        {% endif %}
        {%- endfor -%}
    </div>
</section>

<section class="cta">
    <h2>Let's Work Together</h2>
    <p>I'm always interested in hearing about new projects and opportunities.</p>
    <a href="/contact" class="button primary">Get in Touch</a>
</section> 

